In clinical practice, spondylolisthesis is used synonymously with anterolisthesis. Often, particularly in the lower lumbar spine, it is due to spondylolysis (pars interarticularis defects). The MP term defintion includes both directions whereas the HPO term definition specifies anterior slippage due to complete bilateral fractures of the pars interarticularis.
